main event: A 14-year-old boy reported seeing an object with red and flashing lights over Hibbing, Minnesota on November 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object was observed low on the horizon, appearing larger than a star but smaller than a plane.
The object was seen moving up and down for about 6 minutes.
The witness stated that an aircraft could have accounted for the sight, but the data was somewhat confusing.
The witness had not seen this or a similar object before.
The witness reported the sighting to Project Blue Book.
sighted object: an object with red and flashing lights
